# Login Procedure

    1. Login to EC2 server using Public IP.
    2. ssh -i <key-pair-Location> ubuntu@<Public-IP>
    3. java --version 
    4. sudo -i 
    5. systemctl status jenkins --> press "Q" to quit
    6. ls /var/lib/jenkins --> Jenkins Home directory. 
    7. id jenkins --> Jenkins user
    8. ls -ld /var/lib/jenkins 

# Login to Jenkins 

    1. Copy the public ip of EC2 instance. 
    2. Open browser window and place <http://<public-IP>:8080
    3. Fetch the initial password from - /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
    4. Instal suggested Plugins 
    5. Create a user and set the password
    6. Set the Jenkins URL - as your EC2 instance public IP will change when its powered off and on.
        There is known bug, so as a workaround, set some name instead of IP. If this step is not done, your jenkins server may face slowness. 
